description.plain: Maude Latour is a singer and songwriter, as well as a pop phenomenon. She was born in Sweden, lived in London, and went to school in Hong Kong before she moved to Manhattan for high school. She currently attends Columbia University in New York City, majoring in philosophy. Some of her hit songs include Starsick and Shoot and Run, and she released her first EP, Starsick, in 2019. Her most recent release is the single One More Weekend, which was released about 2 months after Furniture, a fan favorite. Block Your Number, her personal favorite song that she has written so far, came out on 9/25/20
